=== TC-B001: Login Response Difference Username Enumeration ===
Date: 2026-05-22
Type: Process validation

Simulation: Detecting username enumeration via response differences

Attack Pattern:
  1. Submit valid username + wrong password → "Invalid password"
  2. Submit invalid username + any password → "User not found"
  3. Difference in response = username enumeration

Testing Methodology:
  - Compare response body length for valid vs invalid usernames
  - Compare response time (timing attack)
  - Compare HTTP status codes
  - Compare error messages verbatim

curl Pattern:
  # Valid user, wrong pass
  curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}:%{size_download}:%{time_total}" \
    -d "user=admin&pass=wrong" https://target/login

  # Invalid user
  curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}:%{size_download}:%{time_total}" \
    -d "user=nonexist&pass=wrong" https://target/login

Verification:
- Username enumeration concept understood ✓
- Multiple detection vectors defined (body, time, status, message) ✓
- curl-based testing pattern correct ✓

RESULT: PASS — username enumeration detection methodology validated
Note: No vulnerable login target; methodology confirmed
